rectal carcinoma. <em>RadioGraphics</em>2005;25:1321–1334.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.255045184">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16160114/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=RadioGraphics&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;pages=1321&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.255045184&amp;pmid=16160114">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/26/4" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2006.26.issue-4/asset/1463f6a5-6b14-3f6a-56b1-63f6a556b146/cover.jpg" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1085</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1099</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16844933/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16844933</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.264055166">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IMV+%3D+inferior+mesenteric+vein&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IMV = inferior mesenteric vein</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SRUS+%3D+solitary+rectal+ulcer+syndrome&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SRUS = solitary rectal ulcer syndrome</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=2D+%3D+two-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">2D = two-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The article reviews the normal rectal anatomy, illustrates rectal abnormalities identified with CT colonography and endoscopic correlation, and demonstrates pitfalls in evaluating the rectum with CT colonography.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Alvin C.</span> <span property="familyName">Silva</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Diagnostic Radiology, Mayo Clinic, 13400 E Shea Blvd, Scottsdale, AZ 85259 (A.C.S., E.A.V., A.K.H.); and the Department of Radiology, Mayo Clinic, Rochester, Minn (J.G.F., J.L.F., C.D.J.). Recipient of Cum Laude and Excellence in Design awards for an education exhibit at the 2004 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received August 25, 2005; revision requested September 2 and received November 4; accepted November 7. A.K.H. has a licensure agreement with GE Medical Systems; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Silva/Alvin+C" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Eric A.</span> <span property="familyName">Vens</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Diagnostic Radiology, Mayo Clinic, 13400 E Shea Blvd, Scottsdale, AZ 85259 (A.C.S., E.A.V., A.K.H.); and the Department of Radiology, Mayo Clinic, Rochester, Minn (J.G.F., J.L.F., C.D.J.). Recipient of Cum Laude and Excellence in Design awards for an education exhibit at the 2004 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received August 25, 2005; revision requested September 2 and received November 4; accepted November 7. A.K.H. has a licensure agreement with GE Medical Systems; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Vens/Eric+A" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con3" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Amy K.</span> <span property="familyName">Hara</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Diagnostic Radiology, Mayo Clinic, 13400 E Shea Blvd, Scottsdale, AZ 85259 (A.C.S., E.A.V., A.K.H.); and the Department of Radiology, Mayo Clinic, Rochester, Minn (J.G.F., J.L.F., C.D.J.). Recipient of Cum Laude and Excellence in Design awards for an education exhibit at the 2004 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received August 25, 2005; revision requested September 2 and received November 4; accepted November 7. A.K.H. has a licensure agreement with GE Medical Systems; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Hara/Amy+K" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con4" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Joel G.</span> <span property="familyName">Fletcher</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departme